==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Levulinic
<hw>Lev`u*lin"ic</hw> <pr>(-l⟦icr⟧n"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or denoting, an acid (called also
<altname>acetyl-propionic</altname> <xex>acid</xex>),
<chform>C5H8O3</chform>, obtained by the action of dilute acids on
various sugars (as levulose).</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>laevulinic</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Levulosan</ent>⟦br⟧
